Sentencas: To develop new anode material for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs), layered perovskite PrBaFe1.75Nb0.25O5+delta (PBFNO) is synthesized and evaluated.
Titulo: Morphology evolution and exsolution mechanism of a partially decomposed anode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: PBFNO is partially decomposed in wet H-2 to form a composite including Fe, Pr2O3, PrBa2NbxFe1-xO6-delta and survival PBFNO.
Titulo: Morphology evolution and exsolution mechanism of a partially decomposed anode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: PBFNO anode not only exhibits good electrochemical performance, but also can keep activating during long-term operation which contributed by decomposition continuously.
Titulo: Morphology evolution and exsolution mechanism of a partially decomposed anode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Numerous nanoparticles are exsolved upon the initial short-term reduction, but they are agglomerated severely after the subsequent long-term annealing.
Titulo: Morphology evolution and exsolution mechanism of a partially decomposed anode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Therefore, exsolution mechanisms for stable parent perovskites and partially decomposed perovskites are investigated, and the difference mainly lies in their metal-oxide interfaces with different strengths.
Titulo: Morphology evolution and exsolution mechanism of a partially decomposed anode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Finally, morphology evolutions of the partially decomposed PBFNO anode under electrochemical conversion and chemical reduction are compared to demonstrate that electrochemical conversion can accelerate the agglomeration of PBFNO anode.
Titulo: Morphology evolution and exsolution mechanism of a partially decomposed anode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This work provides insights into morphology evolution and exsolution mechanism of partially decomposed perovskite anode for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Morphology evolution and exsolution mechanism of a partially decomposed anode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells
